The SB Opportunity Fund is a $100 million venture fund dedicated to supporting and building a community of outstanding Black, Latinx and Native American Delane Parnell , PlayVS An open letter to Black, Latinx, and Native American Founders Disruption as a buzzword is everywhere in venture But what is rarely disrupted is the VC approach Investors often look for patterns, referrals and pedigree to make the investment process efficient, safely fitting into established The unintended consequence is that brilliant founders are often passed This expresses itself in many ways, perhaps none more harmful than the fact that Black, Latinx, and Native American founders are largely left out of the VC We believe this is bad for society and bad for At SoftBank, we look to invest in untapped markets with massive growth We know from decades of experience that finding such markets and executing flawlessly on an idea requires a unique point of view, bold vision, and Underrepresented founders of color inherently bring a unique perspective to any industry they choose, and the daily trials of systemic racism make them for both life and We think more of these founders would build extraordinary companies given the chance, the network and the capital to do Through the SB Opportunity Fund, we are committed to inviting more visionary, underrepresented founders into our global To do that, we are assembling a diverse Investment Committee that includes members from both inside and outside of SoftBank, and looking at early stage investments alongside growth investments for the first time in And through this work, we are committed to demonstrating that there is no tradeoff between diversity and We know that diversity is good for business, and we know that unconventional thinking Our door is wide open for outstanding Black, Latinx, and Native American founders from across the US, with no warm introductions If that describes you, please reach out . blog congress-gives-small-employer-hras-the-green-light 42197 http: www.advisoryassociates.com blog congress-gives-small-employer-hras-the-green-light 42197 Article Highlights: Century Cures Act Background Qualified Small Employer Eligible Employees Reimbursement Limits Transitional Relief Congress has approved the Century Cures Act, which includes a provision allowing small employers to reimburse their employees for medical expenses under a health reimbursement arrangement without being liable for the draconian, $100 per day penalty for violating the Affordable Care Act’s President Obama has indicated his approval of the Background: HRAs do not meet two key requirements of the ACA, as they: Limit the dollar amount of the insured person’s annual benefits and Fail to provide certain services without requiring As a result, under the IRS’ interpretation of the ACA, employers are subject to a $100 per day (maximum $36,500 per year) excise tax penalty per New Law: Effective January 1, , under the Century Cures Act, qualified small employers that have an average of fewer than employees (including employees) and that maintain a qualified HRA will be exempt from the Under this act, a qualified small employer is one that: (1) Employs an average of fewer than employees (including employees) and does not offer a group health plan to its The number of employees is determined by adding up all the hours that employees worked in a given month and dividing by (2) Provides the HRA on the same terms to all eligible Eligible employees all those except: Those who have not completed days of service, Those who have not attained the age of , workers (generally those working an average of less than hours per week), Seasonal workers (generally those employed for 6 months or fewer during the year), Those covered by a collective bargaining unit, and Certain nonresident (3) Entirely funds the HRA (i.e., no contribution is made to the HRA). (4) Only reimburses the employees after being provided with proof of their medical (5) Limits reimbursements to $4,950 ($10,000 where the plan includes family members) per Amounts are subject to inflation adjustments for years after Although this law is effective January 1, , transitional relief is generally provided for any HRA plan beginning on or before December , Any reimbursements that an employee receives from a qualifying HRA are excluded from that employee’s If you have questions, please give the office a Thu, Dec :00:00 GMT Only Days Left for Tax Deductions http: Connect Humanity is building a community of practice and investment vehicles dedicated to supporting, catalyzing, and scaling solutions that address five barriers to internet access: INFRASTRUCTURE Map options to catalyze and scale infrastructure providers, reduce the cost of backhaul, and improve open source technology at key points in the connectivity stack to increase the ease of building AFFORDABILITY & BUSINESS MODELS Index, support, and explain financing models that best support the specific investment needs of digital infrastructure like community networks, , and municipal POLICY Advocate for policies like increased access to spectrum and “dig once” policies which would accelerate the rate at which people get connected, and support the community of people already leading work in this DIGITAL SKILLS Support digital services and digital literacy initiatives at scale (e.g., in schools, on device, and at point of sale) and increase the pipeline of network engineers working in the public CONTENT Share best practices in scaling the production of locally relevant content, which is a critical incentive for getting people to use and pay for the Working with TechSoup’s community of more than 1 million civil society organizations around the world, Connect Humanity will generate insight into what practices might be best scaled and what’s needed where, and implement those learnings, backed by Central to our approach is a focus on supporting a robust ecosystem of actors, blended financing models, policy change, and open Expand the Financial Toolbox Different communities and interventions to expand access require different types of Connect Humanity will leverage creative financing solutions to support partners with grants, working capital, and impact We will also identify opportunities for leveraging existing capital held in various development funds, develop pooled risk and investment models, and partner with governmental Connect Humanity itself will raise and invest both philanthropic and investment Often, funders can only provide massive capital investments, but many organizations doing connectivity work can’t absorb these We aim to serve as the missing middle between philanthropic grants which typically don’t exceed $250,000 and finance ($5 million+) by helping expert organizations scale up sustainably with manageable investments over DCARB breaks up the built up carbon in your engine and purges it via the exhaust We insert a small Hydroxy delivery hose with smaller inner tube to spray our proprietary Cleaning Agents into the engine’s intake at various times during the carbon removal process The DCARB process for Carbon Removal Step 1 Engine is A hose is inserted into the air intake delivering our proprietary blend of , cleaning agents and Hydroxy Cleaning Agents are sprayed into the idling engine for a few The engine is turned off for ten minutes, giving the cleaners time to loosen The intake valves and valve seats The interior walls of the intake manifold Other parts of the engine After ten minutes the engine is started and revved multiple times to eject the dislodged and dissolved carbon via the exhaust Step 2 Home Getchya for Business Driver Sign Up FAQs Home Getchya for Business Driver Sign Up FAQs Home Getchya for Business Driver Sign Up FAQs FAQ s What is Getchya? Getchya is an on demand courier service which allows you to complete tedious tasks with the lift of a We offer various service options to customers such as curbside pickup, having forgotten items delivered to you, and much more! How do I start using Getchya? In order to begin using Getchya, you must first register as a driver on our app (available for IOS and Android). Once registered, you will be required to pass a background check and proceed to be interviewed by one of our regional Once complete, you will be a member of the Getchya team! Pricing on ordering? Getchya relies on an algorithm that covers the cost of gas for each delivery on a per mile Thus, allowing for the % of the total delivery price to be gross profit for each How to place an order? Once you download the Getchya app (available on IOS and Android), you may register as a You will then have the opportunity to input the items or items you wish to have picked up or How to track your order and delivery? Once an order has been placed, you will receive a series of four notifications (when your order has been accepted, when your order has been picked up, when your Getchya driver is near, and when your item has been delivered). You can also monitor your Getchya driver with live updates in the app What is the familiarity plan? Once you place your first order as a Getchya customer, you will have the option to have the same driver deliver your items again if you were satisfied with how your delivery was carried You will always have the option to use the driver of your choice, you can even book them in advance! How do you report a problem with a delivery order? If you are not satisfied with how your order was carried out you can file a claim, and the Getchya team will investigate any wrongdoings or If the investigation concludes that there has been any issues on our end, the customer will be Why does it take so long to find a driver? After placing a pickup request it can sometimes take a few minutes to find a driver, as it is scanning for all drivers in the Please do not close out of the app and restart until you are given a “no drivers in the area” Then you can replace the order How much information should I provide for a driver? Homepage Heron Point Home Fall Prevention ROI Calculator Science Blog More Schedule a Demo Artificial Intelligence To Prevent Falls Predict Falls Before They Happen with Our Patent Pending Technology Detect The Heron Point Fall Prevention System requires only a single camera placed in a common This camera then passively monitors residents’ gait on a daily From this data, the system quantifies walk features for each resident, such as step length and Report Based on existing clinical research, these features and their rate of change are combined to determine which residents are likely to have a fall in the coming A report with this list of residents is sent to facility staff on a weekly Prevent Staff then put targeted preventative measures in place in order to help those who are likely to suffer a fall (such as physical therapy appointments, walking aids, or medication changes). Immediate alerting is also available for rapid increases in fall risk, such as in cases where medication dosage may be Detect Fall Risk with a Single Camera In order to track resident gaits, the system requires a single device to be placed in a common area where residents are likely to pass through on a daily basis, such as the entrance to a dining The device is minimal in size and installation takes only a matter of Installation requires access to , a standard outlet, and a list of all ​ An algorithm on the device detects when someone walks by it when this happens, the device records a clip of the person The device then sends this data to a secure, AWS cloud server for future ​ When a new clip is sent to the secure servers, key features (such as step length and walking speed) are extracted from the From these features, a fall risk score is The system then assigns this fall risk score to a resident by using the gait The details of a person’s gait are unique to them, much like a On a weekly basis, a report is generated of fall risk scores and changes in fall risk score for all A link to this report is then emailed to facility Reports can be accessed through a secure, web ​ ​ Avoid wearables or large camera systems for fall prevention, both of which invade resident privacy and require constant, expensive Return on Investment Resident Turnover The annual resident turnover across all assisted living residences stands at an astounding %. A large part of this turnover is due to residents requiring more intensive care as the result of a fall ​ The average assisted living facility will have residents fall per of these falls will lead to a serious injury and the resident requiring more intensive The average cost to replace a resident is over $13 This leads to $230,000 total costs per a year from falls per By preventing falls, the Fall Prevention System can save the typical facilities over $100k per year in resident turnover ​ ​ Complete ROI Calculation For an ROI calculation, see our ROI Calculator . When we are living in a constant state of stress, two critical things occur we make it more difficult for our immune system to keep us health and we make poor Which makes us weak and much easier to control and PROBLEM ONE: When stress hormones are released our immune system cannot operate as it We were born survivors , our stress hormones keep us alive when we re in danger Fight , Run or Hide . However, we are not living with a monster in the closet, job, mortgage, boss, an election year, or quick scroll of social media can make us feel this Stress can be a great motivator - but it does a serious doozy on quality of life , how quickly we age and our ability to heal . Our already and undernourished immune system becomes compromised Our ability to fight off new challenges introduced becomes minimized Our immune systems ability to continue fending off the poor choices that we ve made in our past begin to fail PROBLEM TWO: Many of us have acquired an addiction to these stress When we are living in " survival mode ," - it is almost impossible for us to tap into the FORCE of our CREATIVE Spending the majority of our day, over time, prevents us many of us from identifying our unique gift . There are so many problems in the world today , imagine how many can be solved if more of us shake free of this survival dynamic -- turning our problems into gifts , and evolving our gifts into super powers - that serve the greater good --with pure intentions of helping others . ™ is how we chose to add value to the collective of humanity How can we make a difference? What can we do to help the individual elevate? How amazing would it be if everyone found that one thing they truly love? How beautiful would it be if that one thing was enough to provide a good living? Replace Fear, With Confidence We know we can t solve this stress pandemic that everyone has been living in - for most of their But there was one thing within our capabilities, we were already on top of it for those we love most, and the creator compelled us to We found a harmonic balance between the left and the right - led by the most limitless force in the universe, unconditional We the most comprehensive immune supplement in the We merged the best of two It truly is, but no one knows about it, Ignite The Human Spirit We are not a big We don t have a big influencer capable of shining attention on what we ve We did not raise millions of We do not have a digital army, division, or platoon promoting this, just a small band of brothers and aligned with the This project is led by this single dad, who s been through hell and Who s been living in a lockdown for close to 7 Who s lived through rock bottom, losing everything but the will to rise above, and the belief that the lessons learned -- were meant for more than just Shine a Light We were born with the super powers to heal, adapt and We decided, collectively, that there was no way we would standby and watch our fellow the constant recipient of coordinated distraction, confusion, and negativi

Getting started with the API - PDFBlade Home Features Pricing Docs Sign In Sign Up Menu Home Features Pricing Documentation Sign In Sign Up Contents Overview Getting Started Basic Usage Parameter Details Code Examples File Storage Support Documentation How to use PDFBlade Overview Welcome to the PDFBlade documentation! This page and its sections contain all of the information you need to get started consuming the API, converting your website links and raw HTML to formatted Use the links in the sidebar to skip through the different sections of this documentation, or continue scrolling Getting Started In order to start using the API, you ll have to register for an account on the You can click the Sign Up button at the very of this page, or go to the link here . Once your account has been created, you ll be taken to the From there, you can view your API access key by clicking the Show Key button in the dashboard This will reveal the key that you ll need to make calls to the API, as we ll explain further Additionally, when your account was created, you were gifted free conversion These are used to make calls to the API, and are spent when a website or raw HTML has been converted successfully to a Only a single credit is used per conversion regardless of any options set, and by default you ll be notified via email when your account starts to run Additional conversion credits can then be purchased through your dashboard in the billing section . Basic Usage After you ve obtained your authorization key, you can start making calls to the API right Authentication is possible in two ways: By setting the header and using your key as the value By including a key parameter in the request with its value Calls to the API may also be made via either POST or GET The command below is probably the most basic call you can make to the After it completes the GET request, it will return back an Amazon S3 url containing converted into a Bash curl https: pdfblade.com api convert https: google.com&key=my-key-here&store=true And that same command as a POST request looks like this: Bash curl --data="key=my-key-here&store=true&url=https: google.com" https: pdfblade.com api convert Parameter Details Listed below are all of the possible parameters you can include in your calls to the PDFBlade API, along with their All of them work as either parts of the body of a POST request, or tacked on as query variables if you re using the GET request If you have a request for a new option or any suggestions for the parameters that are currently available, please don t hesitate to contact us at . store Required: no Type: boolean Default: false Used to determine whether or not the compiled PDF is cached and stored in Amazon If you set this to true , we will store your PDF on our Amazon S3 bucket and return back a URL that remains active for Otherwise, you will get back the full PDF binary as a You can check your account dashboard to see if stored files are still format Required: no Type: string Default: Letter The paper format and size of the individual pages in the compiled Available options are as follows: Letter , Legal , Tabloid , Ledger , A0 , A1 , A2 , A3 , A4 , A5 , or A6 margins Required: no Type: string Default: 0 The margins (in inches) that are set around the individual pages in the compiled You can pass in a single value like 3 , which will give you a margin of 3 inches around the Alternatively, you can use two values separated by a comma like 3,5 for top bottom and left right respectively, or four like 1,3,1,5 for top, right, bottom, and left background Required: no Type: boolean Default: false Determines whether the background of the website is rendered in the By default, it is Set this to true in order to include it in your landscape Required: no Type: boolean Default: false Determines whether the rendered PDF will be in landscape By default, PDFs are returned in portrait mode, but set this to true to change it to pages Required: no Type: string Default: (null) Allows you to control what pages are returned in the compiled You can pass in a single value like 2 which will only return the second page, or a range of pages like . If you request a page that doesn t exist in the final PDF, it will return media Required: no Type: string Default: screen Gives you the ability to spoof the media agent that the site or HTML is rendered Possible values are screen , speech , and print . userAgent Required: no Type: string Default: Chromium Gives you the ability to spoof the browser s User Agent string sent to the requested site being timeout Required: no Type: integer Default: Sets a limit (in seconds) of how long the renderer will wait for the requested site before timing out and returning back a If a site times out before it is rendered, a conversion credit will not be The minimum for this is 5 and the maximum is . delay Required: no Type: integer Default: 0 Sets a delay (in seconds) that the renderer will wait before beginning to convert the site
